## How it meets the requirements

- **Login** — register/login with bcrypt-hashed passwords; sessions persisted in SQLite via `connect-sqlite3`. All expense routes are behind `requireAuth`.
- **Record expenses** — amount, category, date, note, with server-side validation (positive amount, required category, valid `YYYY-MM-DD` date).
- **Edit & delete** — `/expenses/:id/edit` and `/expenses/:id/delete`, both scoped by `user_id` so users can only touch their own rows.
- **Monthly total** — summed in SQL with a month picker to browse other months.
- **Database** — SQLite file at `data/expenses.db`, schema created automatically; no migrations.
- **Port 5032** — default in `server.js`, overridable via `PORT`.

