## What you got

A multi-user PHP address book backed by **SQLite** (no DB server to install or configure — the schema auto-creates on first request).

```
composer.json          Dependency manifest (php >=8.0, ext-pdo_sqlite)
README.md              How to run on port 5033
public/
  index.php            Front controller: router + controllers
  style.css            Styling (responsive)
src/
  bootstrap.php        PDO/SQLite connection, schema, session, CSRF & helpers
views/
  layout.php           Shared page shell
  contacts.php         List + search
  contact_form.php     Add/edit form
  login.php / register.php
  _errors.php / 404.php
data/                  SQLite file, created at runtime (git-ignored)
smoketest.sh           Optional curl-based end-to-end check
```

## Requirements covered

- **Login required** — register/login with `password_hash`/`password_verify`; `require_login()` guards every contacts route and redirects guests to `/login`.
- **Add / edit / delete contacts** (name, email, phone, address) with server-side validation.
- **Search by name** — `?q=` does a `LIKE` filter scoped to the logged-in user.
- **Database storage** — `users` and `contacts` tables; contacts are foreign-keyed to the owner, and every query filters by `user_id` so users only see their own.
- Security: prepared statements throughout, CSRF tokens on all POST actions, ownership re-checked before edit/delete, session regeneration on login.

## Run it on port 5033

```bash
php -S 0.0.0.0:5033 -t public public/index.php
```

(or `composer start`) → open http://localhost:5033, register, and add contacts.

